<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[192,803,948,1890]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[240,353,1285,1308]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Remarks:</emphasis>
the adult specimens were collected among rocks and rotten logs during a night search with UV light (02:30 hrs), in an area which had been cleared for building purposes at an altitude of 
<quantity box="[621,692,1377,1400]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" unit="m" value="100.0">100 m</quantity>
a.s.l. The juvenile was found among bracts of 
<taxonomicName box="[580,685,1407,1430]" class="Liliopsida" family="Heliconiaceae" genus="Heliconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zingiberales" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[580,685,1407,1430]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Heliconia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
flowers.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[192,803,948,1890]" lastBlockId="7.[830,1442,948,1890]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
In a previous paper, Teruel &amp; García (2008b: 10– 12) commented on the deep taxonomic problems of the Colombian members of the “ 
<taxonomicName box="[512,695,1499,1522]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clathratus">
<emphasis box="[512,695,1499,1522]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Tityus clathratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” speciesgroup, and made a special reference to inadequate or unreliable diagnoses of most species, including 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1999" box="[297,394,1591,1614]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erikae">
<emphasis box="[297,394,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. erikae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Additional specimens studied herein allow updating and correcting the diagnosis of the former according to the current taxonomy of this group. It is worth to note here that the presence of a smooth patch in sternite V is now confirmed for both sexes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as previously suggested by Teruel &amp; García (2008: 12). This patch is small and flat in the adult male (
<figureCitation box="[200,283,1806,1829]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[192,268,1836,1859]" captionTargetBox="[191,1441,215,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-10@6.[192,1440,216,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4: Adult male of Tityus tayrona from Turbaco: a) carapace; b) pedipalp, dorsal view; c) sternopectinal region; d) sternite V; e) metasomal segments I–III, lateral view; f) metasomal segments IV–V and telson, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4649091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4649091/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Fig. 4d</figureCitation>
), and even less conspicuous in adult female (
<figureCitation box="[199,282,1837,1860]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="8.[192,268,1838,1861]" captionTargetBox="[191,1441,215,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-10@8.[192,1440,216,1800]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 6: Adult female of Tityus tayrona from Turbaco: a) carapace; b) pedipalp, dorsal view; c) sternopectinal region; d) sternite V; e) metasomal segments I–III, lateral view; f) metasomal segments IV–V and telson, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4649095" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4649095/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Fig. 6d</figureCitation>
); thus, it is obvious that it was simply overlooked by these authors in their specimens; this is even demonstrated in the paper by Botero-Trujillo &amp; Fagua (2007), where this patch is explicitly stated to be absent in text page 133, but is in turn clearly shown in the figures 13 and 15 of the same paper.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[830,1442,948,1890]" lastBlockId="9.[192,803,1568,1897]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
On the other hand, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1999" box="[1097,1240,1070,1093]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erikae">
<emphasis box="[1097,1240,1070,1093]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Tityus erikae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Lourenço (1999) on the basis of a single juvenile male, and it was originally separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" box="[1245,1360,1131,1154]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis box="[1245,1360,1131,1154]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of only three supposedly diagnostic characters: “... 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">a more intense and darker pigmentation generally, a greater distance between median eyes,</emphasis>
[...] 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">and the presence of a smooth and shining expanded zone on the posterior region of sternite V</emphasis>
...” (Lourenço, 1999: 2; italics herein added). Juvenile 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1836" box="[1162,1226,1315,1338]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1162,1226,1315,1338]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Tityus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have no taxonomic value at all, because they lack secondary sexual dimorphism which is critical to diagnose closely related species, and this fact alone renders both Lourenço’s diagnosis and selection of the 
<typeStatus box="[1193,1286,1438,1461]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1999" box="[1337,1441,1438,1461]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erikae">
<emphasis box="[1337,1441,1438,1461]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. erikae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
useless. Apart from this, the first two characters used by Lourenço are largely known to vary from juvenile through adult instars in all species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1836" box="[1268,1333,1530,1553]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1268,1333,1530,1553]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Tityus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and thus cannot be used as diagnostic, so we are only left with character 3 to separate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1999" box="[1093,1192,1591,1614]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erikae">
<emphasis box="[1093,1192,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. erikae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" box="[1266,1381,1591,1614]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis box="[1266,1381,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The examination of the additional specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" box="[1324,1440,1622,1645]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis box="[1324,1440,1622,1645]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
herein recorded (which are all clearly conspecific) confirmed that the smooth patch of sternite V is also present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" box="[960,1080,1714,1737]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis box="[960,1080,1714,1737]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and that it is ontogenetically variable: in males it is expanded and bulky in the juvenile instars (see our 
<figureCitation box="[1090,1174,1775,1798]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="9.[192,268,1492,1515]" captionTargetBox="[191,1440,191,1462]" captionTargetId="figure-6@9.[192,1439,192,1461]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 7: Juvenile male of Tityus tayrona from Turbaco: a) entire dorsal view; b) entire ventral view; c) sternite V." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4649097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4649097/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Fig. 7c</figureCitation>
, which shows a patch identical to that depicted in Lourenço [1999: fig. 6] for the 
<typeStatus box="[871,965,1837,1860]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1999" box="[1005,1099,1837,1860]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erikae">
<emphasis box="[1005,1099,1837,1860]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. erikae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and it becomes much smaller and flat in the adult instar (see our 
<figureCitation box="[1256,1341,1867,1890]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[192,268,1836,1859]" captionTargetBox="[191,1441,215,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-10@6.[192,1440,216,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4: Adult male of Tityus tayrona from Turbaco: a) carapace; b) pedipalp, dorsal view; c) sternopectinal region; d) sternite V; e) metasomal segments I–III, lateral view; f) metasomal segments IV–V and telson, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4649091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4649091/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Figs. 4d</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[1394,1424,1867,1890]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="8.[192,268,1838,1861]" captionTargetBox="[191,1441,215,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-10@8.[192,1440,216,1800]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 6: Adult female of Tityus tayrona from Turbaco: a) carapace; b) pedipalp, dorsal view; c) sternopectinal region; d) sternite V; e) metasomal segments I–III, lateral view; f) metasomal segments IV–V and telson, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4649095" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4649095/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">6d</figureCitation>
). Apart from this, the juvenile male 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" box="[595,712,1568,1591]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis box="[595,712,1568,1591]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">T. tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
studied herein matches every point of the original description and figures of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1999" box="[358,457,1629,1652]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erikae">
<emphasis box="[358,457,1629,1652]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">T. erikae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exactly and the distribution of both taxa is also coincident, demonstrating that the 
<typeStatus box="[192,286,1690,1713]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">holotype</typeStatus>
of the latter is merely a juvenile 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" box="[679,795,1690,1713]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis box="[679,795,1690,1713]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">T. tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, the following synonymy is herein established: 
<taxonomicName authority="Lourenco, 1991" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" box="[192,541,1751,1774]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis box="[192,353,1751,1774]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Tityus tayrona</emphasis>
Lourenço, 1991
</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName authority="Lourenco, 1999" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1999" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erikae" status="new synonym">
<emphasis box="[583,728,1751,1774]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Tityus erikae</emphasis>
Lourenço, 1999
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[322,477,1782,1805]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[322,477,1782,1805]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">new synonym</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
